Simple impregnation was used to coat the produced NCDs onto bleached cotton fabrics. The photos of the cotton assay stamped with NCDs that were exposed to UV light revealed n unique and bright blue fluorescence (
                        Fig. 4

                        ). Because of its cheapness, simplicity of manufacture, environmental friendliness and convenience of usage, NCDs has the potential for onsite detection of acetone. Under UV light, the blue emission of the white cotton assay was visible to the human eye. All NCDs-imprinted cotton fabrics fluoresced quickly and reversibly under UV irradiation.
